These are some useful scripts:

chroot.sh
	Usage: chroot.sh <device> [program]
	Mounts specified device, binds /proc, /sys and /dev in the mountpoint and executes chroot.
	You can specity $MOUNTOPTIONS to add some mount options, e.g:
	MOUNTOPTIONS=loop,offset=32256  chroot.sh ./disk.hda /bin/sh

cue2flac
	Usage: ./cue2flac <source file> [CUE file] [-s]
	Converts file to FLAC and splits it using CUE sheet.

filebin, omploader, *-uploader
	Usage: $0 <file> [file] ...
	Uploads specified files to the specified site.

flac2mp3
	Usage: flac2mp3 [ -s ] <file1.flac> ... [filen.flac]
	Encodes selected FLAC files (or directories) to MP3.
	Use -s to suspend all external programs output.
	You may also set $LAME variable, for example:
	LAME=-V0 flac2mp3 somefile.flac

flac2ogg
	Usage: flac2ogg [ -s ] <file1.flac> ... [filen.flac]
	Encodes selected FLAC files (or directories) to OGG.
	Use -s to suspend all external programs output.
	You may also set $OGGENC variable, for example:
	OGGENC=-q10 flac2ogg somefile.flac

imagebin
	Usage: imagebin [-s] <file1> ... [filen]
	Upload files to imagebin.ca
	-s: supress all output exept file URLs

*-downloader
	Usage: $0 <URL> [URL] ...
	Downloads files from specified file hosting URLs.

any2ogg
	Splits and converts losless music to OGG Vorbis
